The constitutional issue is actually kind of funny. Police powers are reserved for the states generally but the current broad reading of the commerce clause by the Supreme Court says as long as the policing is limited to acts that affect interstate commerce, it’s ok. So the solution has been to pass whatever bills they want and just add a phrase that says like “when the act has an effect on interstate commerce.”
